img.alt: Thumbnail for version as of 10:18, 30 January 2023

tr.td: Azure claw and fangs are not included in the Flag of New Brunswick according to the official Government of New Brunswick website article on provincial symbols (https://www2.gnb.ca/content/gnb/en/gateways/about_nb/symbols.html).

img.alt: Thumbnail for version as of 22:14, 8 June 2020

tr.td: The flag is a banner of arms, so the lion should be ''armed and langued azure'' as in the coat of arms. Reference image from the Canadian Heraldic Authority: https://reg.gg.ca/heraldry/pub-reg/ProjectPics/i016_19900045_flag_newbrunswick.jpg
